<div class="tw-row-padding tw-padding-64 tw-theme-l1" style="background-color:lightgrey" id="work">
    <div class="tw-twothird">
        <h2>About Us!</h2>
        <p>
            <h2>The Ducken Wellington</h2>
            We are a comfortable, family/farm homestay. Our central heating will keep you cosy during Wellington’s colder and gustier days and nights.
            <br />
            <em>Quality cooked breakfast is included.</em>
            <br />
            There is a comfortable lounge/dining area, including a TV, for your own use. Netflix and Wi-Fi are also available.
            As mentioned, we are only a few minutes walk from the local bus and railway stations.
            We look forward to meeting you on your next visit to Wellington, and making it as comfortable as possible.


            <h3>The space</h3>

            I have two available bedrooms which share one bathroom.
            One room is a queen size room, the other is a king single room with a roll-away for children.<br />
            <br />
            There is a cosy covered sit-out and large deck with garden furniture and BBQ you can use.
            The main lounge/dining area is fully furnished.
            You will be part of our family when you come and stay.
            <br />
            <h3>Guest access</h3>
            As well as the bedrooms, you will have access to open plan kitchen/dining and family room area, as well as a private loung/dining to relax, read, play games, or watch TV.<br />
            <br />
            <h3>Interaction with guests</h3>
            I would be mostly onsite and can help with holiday ideas. I can also pickup from Ferry or Airport if needed, for a minimum fee of $25 - $40<br />
            <br />
            <h4>Other things to note</h4>
            I make my own bread most days and with fresh free range eggs (chickens in the backyard).<br />
            You can have either, a full cooked breakfast of bacon & eggs with toast or continental breakfast, of cereal with homemade preserves and yoghurt.<br />
            Tawa is centrally located to 3 different beaches, only a few minutes drive away with spectacular views and walks.<br />
            We are in a quiet area close to shops and cafés within walking distance and plenty of free parking.<br />
            <br />
            <br />
        </p>
